- Install Npgsql via NuGet: `dotnet add package Npgsql.EntityFrameworkCore.PostgreSQL`
- Update Entity Framework Core to latest version: `dotnet tool update --global dotnet-ef`
- Use the following DbContext configuration:
```csharp
public class MyDbContext : DbContext
{
    public DbSet<MyEntity> MyEntities { get; set; }

    protected override void OnConfiguring(DbContextOptionsBuilder optionsBuilder)
    {
        optionsBuilder.UseNpgsql("Host=myhost;Database=mydatabase;Username=myuser;Password=mypassword");
    }
}
```
- Run migrations: `dotnet ef migrations add InitialCreate`
- Update database schema: `dotnet ef database update`
- Key config options:
  - Connection string
  - Migrations directory
  - Model builder configuration

- **CLI Commands**:
  - `dotnet new webapi -n MyProject`
  - `dotnet add package Npgsql.EntityFrameworkCore.PostgreSQL`
  - `dotnet ef migrations add InitialCreate`
  - `dotnet ef database update`

- **Latest Versions**:
  - .NET Core: 6.0
  - Entity Framework Core: 6.0
  - PostgreSQL: 14

- **Key Config Options**:
  - Connection String in `appsettings.json`: `"DefaultConnection": "Host=localhost;Port=5432;Database=mydatabase;Username=myuser;Password=mypassword"`
  - DbContext Configuration: 
    ```csharp
    public class MyDbContext : DbContext
    {
        public DbSet<MyEntity> MyEntities { get; set; }

        protected override void OnConfiguring(DbContextOptionsBuilder optionsBuilder)
        {
            optionsBuilder.UseNpgsql(Configuration.GetConnectionString("DefaultConnection"));
        }
    }
  ```
  - Migration Configuration: 
    ```csharp
    public class MyDbContext : DbContext
    {
        public DbSet<MyEntity> MyEntities { get; set; }

        protected override void OnModelCreating(ModelBuilder modelBuilder)
        {
            modelBuilder.Entity<MyEntity>(entity =>
            {
                entity.ToTable("MyEntities");
                entity.HasKey(e => e.Id);
            });
        }
    }
  ```
